&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Luis Arce of the Movement for Socialism wins the Bolivian presidential election by a landslide.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&quot;preface&quot; style=&quot;position:relative;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#preface&quot; aria-label=&quot;preface permalink&quot; class=&quot;anchor before&quot;&gt;&lt;svg aria-hidden=&quot;true&quot; focusable=&quot;false&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; version=&quot;1.1&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 16 16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot;&gt;&lt;path fill-rule=&quot;evenodd&quot; d=&quot;M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Preface&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bolivia has a soft spot in my heart, as I spent around 2 months there back in 2016. I met a lot of great people there and had great conversations, despite the language barrier.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Last year, the socialist government led by Evo Morales was violently overthrown; it is speculated that this was caused by a U.S-backed staged coup. As his replacement, a far-right senator, Jeanine Áñez, assumed the presidency. Throughout the year, Bolivia has cycled through protests and counterprotests. As a direct result, there has been escalating political unrest and ethnic tensions leading to more than 30 deaths, most being indigenous pro-Morales protestors.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A few weeks ago, the Bolivian people have spoken, and they have spoken quite loudly. The previously mentioned socialist party has come back into power after a landslide victory in the 2020 Bolivian general election.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Why were they overthrown in the first place? What does it mean for them to be back in power? Why should you care?&lt;/p&gt;
