&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Turns out it’s actually pretty cold in Bolivia during their winters.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&quot;evo-morales-rather-shady-timeline&quot; style=&quot;position:relative;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#evo-morales-rather-shady-timeline&quot; aria-label=&quot;evo morales rather shady timeline permalink&quot; class=&quot;anchor before&quot;&gt;&lt;svg aria-hidden=&quot;true&quot; focusable=&quot;false&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; version=&quot;1.1&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 16 16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot;&gt;&lt;path fill-rule=&quot;evenodd&quot; d=&quot;M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Evo Morales’ rather shady timeline&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Evo Morales of the Movement for Socialism (MAS) party was the first indigenous president of Bolivia, elected for the first time in 2005. His administration emphasized on moving towards a mixed economy (anti-neoliberalism), environmentalism, and social reform.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In Bolivia, presidents are limited to a maximum of &lt;strong&gt;two&lt;/strong&gt; consectutive terms. However, the constitutional court allowed Morales to run for a third consectutive term ruling that his first term did not count towards the limit, since it was before the new constitution was ratified in 2009. Pretty shady stuff, but I guess it makes some sense.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;During his third term, Morales vowed that he would not attempt to run for a fourth term and that he would never consider amending the constitution to allow for this.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;That’s a very oddly specific promise to make to the people.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Did he keep his word? Let’s take a look.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2016&lt;/strong&gt;: A referendum sponsored by the MAS’ attempt to amend the constitution to allow a new limit of three consecutive terms is held. The amendment fails by a slim margin.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;…is this democratic? I guess by definition, a referendum is pretty democratic&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2017&lt;/strong&gt;: Claiming that term limits are human rights violations according to the American Convention on Human Rights, MAS petitions to the Plurinational Constitutional Court to abolish term limits. The court accepts the petition, allowing Morales to submit his application for presidential candidacy to the Bolivian Electoral Tribunal. The application is approved by the tribunal. It is likely that both courts had a strong majority of Morales loyalists.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;…that’s not very democratic&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2019&lt;/strong&gt;: Morales wins the election for his fourth presidential term by a very small margin. Protests and counterprotests begin in Bolivia as the people begin to have suspicions about electoral fraud.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I think we can say that he did &lt;em&gt;not&lt;/em&gt; keep his word.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&quot;the-coup-détat&quot; style=&quot;position:relative;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#the-coup-d%C3%A9tat&quot; aria-label=&quot;the coup détat permalink&quot; class=&quot;anchor before&quot;&gt;&lt;svg aria-hidden=&quot;true&quot; focusable=&quot;false&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; version=&quot;1.1&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 16 16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot;&gt;&lt;path fill-rule=&quot;evenodd&quot; d=&quot;M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;The coup d’état&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span
